featured_reviews.review_id:
This is one of my favourite place for coffee, ofcourse during mostly during month start, not month end. Yeah Starbucks is a brand but it is pricey and from past few years prices of coffee and other things have gone up considerably.

Coffee is good, but can be better given the premium they charge. The cold coffee was also ok types, I expected them to add sugar in the cold coffee atleast, We spent almost 20 minutes and 4-5 sachets of sugar to make it taste better. Pretty difficult to mix sugar in cold coffee, they should know about it.

The sandwich was also okayish, newyork cheese cake was yummy. So overall it was ok experience. I will definitely rethink going Starbucks next time and give chance to new independent cafes, that gave quality for the price.

This space is good for couples and big groups. I was missing the light music and the cosy sittings that other Starbucks outlets in Pune offers.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Starbucks!!!! And I must say, it was an amazing experience! The moment I walked in, I was greeted with a warm and welcoming atmosphere, and the delicious aroma of freshly brewed coffee.
The menu had a great selection of drinks to choose from, and the quality of the coffee was outstanding. I ordered a caramel macchiato and it was perfectly crafted with just the right amount of sweetness.
What really stood out to me, however, was the exceptional customer service. The staff was friendly, knowledgeable and went out of their way to make sure I had a great experience. They even took the time to explain different drink options and make recommendations based on my preferences.
Overall, I highly recommend Starbucks to anyone looking for a great cup of coffee and a wonderful atmosphere. The exceptional customer service and high quality beverages make it a must-visit destination for coffee lovers.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I ordered 2 caramel frappes but when I made the payment and checked the bill, they changed my order to caramel Java chip when I had specifically mentioned that I wanted only caramel. When I went to complain to the guy, he had the cheek to argue and said that I wouldn't get a refund.

Edit: Visited again as I had a coupon for a drink at 190 rupees. I ordered vanilla sweet cream. They filled more than half of my cup with ice cubes (I've attached pictures but you can't see it very clearly) and the coffee wasn't even good. You'd get the idea that the drink is sweet from the name, but it's quite the opposite. It was really bitter and there wasn't a hint of vanilla and no cream either. Pretty bad.

featured_reviews.review_id:
The Starbucks located in Kothrud near Karishma Society is undoubtedly a hidden gem in the neighborhood, and I have thoroughly enjoyed my visits there. This two-story Starbucks establishment offers a delightful ambiance that combines modern design with a cozy atmosphere, making it an ideal spot for both catching up with friends and finding a moment of solitude.

One of the standout features of this particular Starbucks is the availability of personal parking. In a bustling area like Kothrud, where parking can often be a challenge, having dedicated parking for customers is a major convenience. It not only saves time but also ensures a stress-free visit.

The service at this Starbucks branch is consistently impressive. The staff is not only friendly but also highly efficient. They manage to maintain a perfect balance between taking orders swiftly and preparing drinks with care. I've never experienced any unnecessary delays during my visits.

As for the beverages, Starbucks always lives up to its reputation for offering a wide range of high-quality coffee and non-coffee options. Whether you're a fan of their signature lattes or prefer a refreshing iced tea, there's something for everyone. The coffee is consistently well-brewed and pairs wonderfully with their delectable snacks.

In conclusion, the Starbucks near Karishma Society in Kothrud has managed to create a welcoming and convenient haven for coffee enthusiasts. With its personal parking, pleasant ambiance, and excellent service, it has become a favorite spot for many in the area, including myself. I highly recommend a visit to experience the fantastic vibe and enjoy your favorite Starbucks treats.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I know most of u are big fans of the chain, but I'm not really a fan. I think it's overpriced, the coffee is mediocre, and the atmosphere is too pretentious for my taste.

I remember one time when we were all out with my friends wife, and she insisted that we go to Starbucks. I didn't really want to go, but I didn't want to be rude. So we went, and I ended up spending way too much money on a cup of coffee that my wife, me or that friend of mine didn't even like.

I then realized that that there are fans of this place who mostly I feel are just being pretentious. Lousy cow thinks that drinking Starbucks makes her seem more sophisticated, but I think it just makes her look like a snob.

I'm not saying that you can't like Starbucks. If you enjoy the coffee and the atmosphere, then that's great. But for me, it's just not worth the money.

I'd rather go to a local coffee shop where I can get a better cup of coffee for a fraction of the price.
